header.gameNote: ODWALLA CLASSIC AT SAN FRANCISCO CA

article.description: Samantha Mahoney scored 17 points in Kentucky's 78-59 victory over Southern Illinois in the consolation game of the Odwalla Classic.
article.headline: Kentucky earns consolation victory at Odwalla Classic
article.linkText: Kentucky earns consolation victory at Odwalla Classic
article.story:
SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Samantha Mahoney scored 17 points and Sarah Elliott had 12 points and 11 rebounds in Kentucky's 78-59 victory over Southern Illinois in the consolation game of the Odwalla Classic on Saturday night.

Nastassia Alcius scored 11 points in a reserve role as Kentucky (3-2) recovered from Friday's 86-70 upset loss to Delaware with a solid victory over the Salukis (1-4) in the tournament hosted by the University of San Francisco.

The Wildcats (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today; No. 20 AP) led 45-32 at halftime while making 52 percent of their shots, then coasted to the win while forcing 23 turnovers.

Carlai Moore scored 27 points on 10-of-13 shooting for Southern Illinois, and Debbie Burris hit four 3-pointers on the way to 18 points.
